{
    "name": "Giant Whiptail Centipede",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> temperate or warm forests or underground <br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, pair, or colony (3\u20136) <br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Poison (Ex) </b>Bite\u2014injury; <i>save </i>Fort DC 17; <i>frequency </i>1/round for 6 rounds; <i>effect </i>1d4 Dex; <i>cure </i>1 save. The save DC is Constitution-based. <br/><br/><b>Tail Slap (Ex)</b> A giant whiptail centipede\u2019s tail slap deals nonlethal damage and gains no bonus from its Strength score on damage dealt."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Whiptail centipedes are carrion eaters, though corpses large enough to satiate them are a rarity. Corpses of Huge or larger creatures left to rot often attract whiptail centipedes, who viciously defend their bounty against any who would intrude upon their lairs."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>An elephantine centipede scurries about, its double tail lashing angrily behind it. </i>",
